# linux standard streams

stdin	0
stdout	1
stderr	2


# redirect

stdout	1>
stderr	2>

## single redirect examples:
<command>.sh 1> stdout_file
<command>.sh 2> stderr_file

## multiple redirect examples:
### to separate files
<command>.sh 1> stdout_to_file 2> stderr_file
### to single file
<command>.sh > stdout_to_file 2&>1
#### note:
'>' is short for '1>'
'2&>1' means: redirect stream 2 to the same destination as stream 1

## no output example:
<command>.sh > /dev/null 2&>1
#### note:
redirecting to /dev/null means: no output anywhere

